"Use" means to access, download, copy, install, run, execute, test, evaluate,
study, modify, compile, build, deploy, or create derivative works of the
Software.

"Internal Users" means your employees, officers, directors, contractors,
consultants, and Affiliates who access or use the Software solely on your
behalf and solely for your own internal business operations.

"Affiliate" means an entity that directly or indirectly controls, is controlled
by, or is under common control with you.

"Permitted Internal Use" means Use of the Software by you and your Internal
Users solely for your own internal operations, workflows, administration,
automation, research, development, testing, security, reporting, analytics,
or other internal business purposes.

Permitted Internal Use includes production use inside your own organization,
including by for-profit companies, provided that the Software is not offered,
hosted, operated, managed, distributed, exposed, or made available to third
parties as part of a product, platform, service, SaaS, managed service,
service-provider offer, outsourcing offer, consulting offer, reseller offer,
or other commercial offering.

"Third Party" means any person or entity other than you, your Affiliates,
and your Internal Users.

"External User" means any Third Party, including any customer, client,
prospect, partner, supplier, vendor, reseller, distributor, or public user.

"Commercial Service Use" means directly or indirectly monetizing the Software,
or making the Software available to Third Parties, including by offering,
selling, reselling, sublicensing, distributing, hosting, managing, operating,
supporting, integrating, embedding, white-labeling, outsourcing, providing
access to, or otherwise using the Software as part of a paid or monetized
product, service, SaaS, managed service, platform, marketplace, consulting
service, implementation service, integration service, reseller offer,
distributor offer, agency offer, freelancer offer, or service-provider offer.

Commercial Service Use includes use where the Software is a material part of
a paid or monetized offering, even if the Software itself is not separately
itemized, separately charged, or separately branded.

"Managed Service" means any arrangement in which a person or entity hosts,
runs, operates, administers, maintains, monitors, supports, customizes, or
provides access to the Software for or on behalf of a Third Party, whether
or not the Software is branded as synit.io software.

"Attribution Notice" means a notice substantially similar to:

    "This software uses [PROJECT NAME] by synit.io."

or, where technically reasonable:

    "Powered by [PROJECT NAME] by synit.io."

